                    "text": "A spellcaster can target a devourer with a mental spell, <a aonid=\"19\" game-obj=\"Spells\"><i>banishment</i></a>, <a aonid=\"21\" game-obj=\"Spells\"><i>bind soul</i></a>, <a aonid=\"82\" game-obj=\"Spells\"><i>divine decree</i></a>, <a aonid=\"86\" game-obj=\"Spells\"><i>divine wrath</i></a>, <a aonid=\"225\" game-obj=\"Spells\"><i>possession</i></a>, <a aonid=\"301\" game-obj=\"Spells\"><i>spirit blast</i></a>, or <a aonid=\"303\" game-obj=\"Spells\"><i>spirit song</i></a> to attempt to counteract the devourer\u2019s Devour Soul effect. If this counteract attempt succeeds, the trapped soul is released (though the creature remains dead), and the devourer can\u2019t use any soul charges from the creature. Devourers are otherwise immune to these spells."
                }
